sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2110005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PETase gene encodes the PETase enzyme which can degrade PET to terephthalic acid (TPA) and ethylene glycol (EG) with another enzyme MHETase. However, the product TPA can cause inhibition of the reaction and slow down it. This expression system consists of the TPA inducible Leader sequence, the enhanced promoter PGK1(BBa_K2110012), the PETase gene(BBa_K2110800) and Terminator CYC1(BBa_K2110000). It can be induced by product TPA so that this is a positive feedback system. This system is used in Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Le He

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2110000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CYC1 Terminator is widely used in Saccharomyces cerevisiae. It is a composite part in many vectors of Saccharomyces cerevisiae like plasmid pYES2. Amplifying it by PCR and link it after your protein coding sequence is also feasible if you want to express the gene in Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haoran Ding
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from genome sequence of Saccharomyces cerevisiae
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There is no neccessary consideration in detailed design of the sequence

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2110012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter is a enhanced promoter used in Saccharomyces cerevisiae. It regulates the 3-phosphoglycerate kinase (PGK1) gene in Saccharomyces cerevisiae. This promoter can be used in both plasmid and genome of Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Le He

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2110001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence comes from RhodococcusjostiiRHA1. Rhodococcus owns the ability of degrading terephthalic acid (TPA), this pathway is regulated by many genes and some of them can be induced by TPA. The inducing effect is based on a regulatory proteintpaR, which can bind this sequence at the existence of TPA and induce the expression of downstream gene. This sequence should be placed before the sequence of promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Le He
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the genome of RhodococcusjostiiRHA1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence is very short so if the gel recycling is necessary, the agarose concentration should be increased.
